<br>
The fall out in AoV from this event was almost total.  Even though it was all mostly uninformed speculation, misunderstandings, and general jump to conclusions, it brought out some underlying issues within the guild that had appearantly been festering and had gone unnoticed.  <br>
<br>
The post I add here now was meant to stay within the guild to help bolster a new era in rebuilding, I share this with you for the sole purpose of understanding and compassion on your part to see where we are now and what we now face as a guild.  Do not judge us on actions past regardless of what others say but rather on where we go from here.  TY for you time, hope you enjoy the read.<br>
<br>
State of the Guild Address!<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 As many of you will notice, the board seems a little sparse on content. I have taken the time to delete all the negative post's and all the post's asking what's going on. This was done to usher in a new era of positive thinking on the part of all members, instead of focusing on what has transpired in the past few months. Bish, when you get the time, make a retired section so that we can honor those of our valued members are not forgotten nor their role trivialized by hard feelings for actions in the past.<br>
<br>
As to our current state, we are in transition as can be clearly seen by all. Gone is the time for grouping outside the guild unless no one else is on. Gone is the time for hard feelings because someone left. Gone is the time to sit doing nothing complaining or asking what now. Now is the time to act and act as one voice we shall!<br>
<br>
We are currently shorty in numbers in many ways. We need clerics, chanters, rangers, rogues, wizzards, shammies, beastlords, mage's, SK's, pally's, bards. In short ALL class's are open for recruitment. For the time being twinks again will be totally frowned upon. This is your game and your game time to do with as you please, but I am asking for a commitment from all of you that if you can not 2 box, please refrain from playing a twink no matter the situation. Twinks will not rebuild the guild. Cooperation and communication will. When looking at someone to join the guild, its all fair game. You know the over all attitude of the guild and what we look for in a member. If you do not, then ask. Invite at will all willing to take the tag. We can weed out from there. Regardless of anything, a good attitude and willingness to learn will be kept over a bad attitude and huge game knowledge. Id rather take the time teaching someone the game and how to play than to spend the time in tell hell because someone can not control their actions.<br>
<br>
<br>
Oh Brell, we come to you in time of great need. We come to you not as individuals, but as a group, an entity, a family, seeking your guidance. There is a dragon among us, one that has great power born not of the natural creation of Norrath, but born from our own minds.<br>
This dragon is the spawn of our fears, our uncertainties, our doubts in the goodness of others. He has taken several of our family from us in a most brutal way never to be heard from again. Others he has lead astray with the promise of a greener pasture in another existence. We have fallen pray to our own creation.<br>
We ask of you now for the power and the strength that only the gods themselves posses to help us rise above this terrible dragon and to forge on in a new era of cooperation, understanding, and communication. Lead us down the path of glory oh great and might Brell, show us the faith and direction we will need to posess in order to slay this dragon of ill intent. Let it be known to all that we shall not fall, we shall not die, we shall rise like the Phoenix from the ash's and capture the place in the history of Norrath that we so rightly deserve. <br>
Give me the strength and the wisdom to guild our family down the path of righteousness. To do the right thing to ourselves and to our fellow citizens of Norrath. Help me oh Brell to stand tall and strong in the face of adversity and accusation to stare down the overwhelming obstacles that will lye in our path and lead on to victory. Help us Brell, to become again what we once were. A family.<br>
<br>
<br>
Mcpally Doon<br>
Guild Leader(interim)<br>
Asylum of Vengeance<br>
60 Crusader of Quellious <br>
<br>
Please direct all questions, comments, etc to me personally in game and not on the board.  We have taken a hard enough hit already and now are trying to start over.  <br>
